cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.DS

This paper deals with the development of a way to automatically model log files and detect outlier traces in the data. The use of Dynamic Bayesian Networks to model the normal behavior found in log files suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The development of a new algorithm that is able to learn a model of a log file starting from the data itself suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The focus on detecting outlier traces in the data suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The fact that the paper deals with log files suggests that it could also belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. Finally, the use of Bayesian Networks suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
